title: Comment on The Mississippi Stingray has a Message for the BBN by Webb55
text:
Posted in Football , Main | 5 Responses @SteveRay24 
The Mississippi Stingray is back, and he’s ready to take on the Big Blue Nation. I thought there wasn’t anything worth seeing in Starkville, until I saw him posing in front of his own billboard. 
He normally sticks to talking trash via YouTube, so this new venture is a little out of his element. But that doesn’t mean he didn’t take the time to rant about the Cayts on YouTube, with the help of Peter Griffin. 
My mission in Starkville is now clear: find the Mississippi Stingray. Article written by Nick Roush "Look upon the doughnut, and not upon the hole." @RoushKSR 5 responses to “The Mississippi Stingray has a Message for the BBN” huck October 22, 2015 at 9:21   
That is a good question. Are we going to play some ball or pretend its only Eastern. Well we could just be pretty. yodelaheyoo October 22, 2015 at 9:28   
The mission should be to have him and Kige Ramsey do the pre-game show together huck October 22, 2015 at 9:33   
I bet that would get some hits. Go CATS Pitino'sLoveChild October 22, 2015 at 10:35   
And that folks, is why finding your mate at a family reunion is a bad idea. I’m guessing Stingray’s family tree is short a few branches. James October 22, 2015 at 10:48   
Virgil needs to lose about 25 pounds of face fat – probably have gravy for blood. 
#fatasshogjowls
